**Enabling Vulnerabilities --- What Makes Each Stage Possible**

  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  **Enabling              **Capability Gained**   **Primary OWASP
  Vulnerability**                                 Category**

  XSS (Stored or          JavaScript execution in A03:2025 Injection
  Reflected) in hook      victim\'s browser       
  delivery page                                   

  No HttpOnly flag on     Session cookies         A02:2025 Cryptographic
  session cookies         readable by hook script Failures

  Browser\'s trusted      Access to internal      A10:2025 SSRF
  network position (by    hosts blocked from      (Server-Side concept
  design)                 internet                applied client-side)

  Command Injection in    Arbitrary OS command    A03:2025 Injection
  internal server         execution on internal   
  (os.popen + input)      server                  
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **The key insight:** no single vulnerability achieves this --- the
  chain requires XSS **and** command injection **and** the browser\'s
  trusted network position. Fixing any one link breaks the chain. This is
  why defence-in-depth matters: HttpOnly cookies limit XSS impact, input
  validation prevents command injection, and network segmentation limits
  lateral movement even if both attacks succeed.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
